<link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/dashboard.css">
<script src="/js/pages/about.js"></script>

<% include parts/navbar.ejs %>

<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-2 sidebar">
      <% include parts/sidebar.ejs %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-9 col-sm-offset-3 col-md-10 col-md-offset-2 main">
      <!-- Main content -->
      <h1 class="page-header">About</h1>

      <div class="panel panel-danger">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h3 class="panel-title">Note</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p><strong>Note: </strong>In order to write proper content for this page, it is recommended that the user reads <a href="https://help.github.com/articles/markdown-basics/">this link</a> on the Markdown Formatting Language.  It allows to create blog, italics, headings, etc.  All text inserted into the box below will be parsed into it's appropriate format on the <a href="/about">About</a> page.</p>
          <p>If you want to play around with more Markdown, or just make sure that what you are inputting is correct, I recommend downloading <a href="http://steventhanna.github.io/proton/">Proton</a>, a Markdown application for Mac, Windows, and Linux.</p>
          <p>Eventually, the about page will migrate into something similar to how blogs are created.  This is only temporary</p>
        </div>
      </div>



      <form>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="introText">Content for Introduction Text on Home Page</label>
          <input id="introText" type="text" class="form-control" value="<%= page.introText %>">
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="aboutText">Content for the About Page</label>
          <textarea id="aboutText" class="form-control" rows="10"><%= about %></textarea>
        </div>
      </form>

      <br />
      <div class="pull-right"><a id="updateAboutButton" class="btn btn-success btn-md">Update About</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
